        "url": "https://twitter.com/bellaqvist/status/1103278736034672641",
        "html": "<blockquote class=\"twitter-tweet\"><p lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\">&quot;A human voice is nicer to listen to than a synthetic one, especially when it is a longer piece,&quot; says <a href=\"https://twitter.com/susieC20?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw\">@susieC20</a>, of <a href=\"https://twitter.com/guardian?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw\">@guardian</a> Voice Labs, but adds the tech knits the synthetic voice together with a human, adding richness to tone and speed etc. <a href=\"https://twitter.com/hashtag/newsrw?src=hash&amp;ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw\">#newsrw</a></p>&mdash; Bella Qvist (@bellaqvist) <a href=\"https://twitter.com/bellaqvist/status/1103278736034672641?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw\">March 6, 2019</a></blockquote>\n<script async src=\"https://platform.twitter.com/widgets.js\" charset=\"utf-8\"></script>\n",
